Allow admins, when viewing issue / workflow transition screens, either use a keyboard shortcut, or a UI element that only appears for them, to ask JIRA why a specific custom field is or is not showing on that screen.

Ideally once they enter this mode they get a list of every custom field in the instance, and can select the one they are wanting to query, at which point it gives them a list of the reason it may or may not be showing up on a screen (is it on that screen, in the right field configuration, does it have a UI component, is it hidden, etc etc) with a tick or a cross next to each to indicate if this is allowing or stopping a field from appearing.

Providing direct links to the section of the admin panel to change this particular setting will let them quickly make changes and fix up custom field visibility issues.

